#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1433
msgid "NOTE: Farmland on a tile prevents any trade bonus from Super Highways."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1472
#, fuzzy
msgid "Pre-Fortress"
msgstr "מבצר"

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1498
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A Pre-Fortress is the groundwork for a Fortress, and in itself does nothing "
"but allow further expansion to a Fortress."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1531
msgid ""
"Fortresses are more permanent forts; construction on them can only begin "
"once the underlying fort is complete. Forts on River tiles cannot be "
"upgraded to Fortresses."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1535
msgid ""
"Units in a fortress receive extra defense (+100%) against land units and "
"boats, and do not count as aggressive if near a friendly city. Any kind of "
"land unit remaining in a fortress for a whole turn without moving recovers a "
"quarter of its hit points."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1570
msgid ""
"An Airbase provides permanent support for air units and missiles. Air units "
"can land and refuel on an Airbase and Paratroopers can be sent from "
"Airbases. "
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1573
msgid ""
"Units in Airbases do not count as aggressive if near a friendly city, and "
"can see further afield. Also, air units recover more hit points (a third per "
"turn, the same as in a city without an Airport)."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1578
msgid ""
"Airbases have efficient anti-air weapons: units in an Airbase receive extra "
"defense (+100%) against air units and missiles. "
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1629
msgid ""
"Ruins mark the former site of a city that was destroyed or abandoned. They "
"have no effect on gameplay other than giving +1 trade bonus for the tile "
"with the ruins."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1658
msgid ""
"Roads allow your land units to move more quickly, and allow wheeled Big Land "
"units such as Chariots and Catapults to travel through otherwise difficult "
"terrain (Mountains, Jungle, and Swamp)."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1733
msgid ""
"With sufficient technology, you may build magnetic levitation systems along "
"your railroad routes. Land units expend no movement points when riding a "
"maglev, you may ride indefinitely. (As may your enemies!)"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1771 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1843
msgid ""
"Roads and railroads can only be built on River tiles if your civilization "
"has learned Bridge Building technology. Fortresses and Airbases cannot be "
"built on River tiles."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1816
msgid ""
"Iron, when found on a Mountain tile, gives 4 more shields. For more "
"information, review the help for the individual tile type."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1836
msgid ""
"Game, when found on a Tundra tile, gives 3 more food and 1 more shield. For "
"more information, review the help for the individual tile type."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1855
msgid ""
"Furs, when found on a Tundra tile, gives 1 more food, 1 more shield, and 3 "
"more trade. For more information, review the help for the individual tile "
"type."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:2000
msgid ""
"Oasis, when found on a Desert tile, gives 3 more food and 4 more trade. For "
"more information, review the help for the individual tile type."
msgstr ""

